  "text": "Regardless of increased computer access and technology development support, technological tools have not been fully harnessed to administer the types of teaching that is supposed to be most influential [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . Regrettably, research shows that the use of Web 3.0/ Web 2.0 tools tends to be of a poor standard (Maddux & Johnson, 2006) . In this section, the researchers view the adoption of Web 3.0/ Web 2.0 from the lens of an educator as mediator of transformation. There is no doubt that educators have improved their individual and skilled uses of technologies, yet many still struggles [CITATION_3] .",
